  "decision_conditions": [
    "The development hereby permitted shall not be carried out except in complete accordance with the details shown on the submitted plans, numbers 2023-13CMR-ADS2-4 and 2023-13CMR-ADS2-5  and shall thereafter be retained/maintained for as long as the development remains in existence.",
    "REASON",
    "To ensure the development complies with the provisions Hillingdon Local Plan Parts 1 (November 2012) and 2 (January 2020) and the London Plan (2021).",
    "The two roof mounted non-illimunated signs (signs 1 and 2 on drawing reference 2023-13CMR-ADS2-4 and 2023-13CMR-ADS2-5 ) shall be removed within two months of the date of this permission.",
    "Reason",
    "The design, appearance and use of materials of the roof mounted signs results in an incongruous and visually intrusive form of development, which fails to harmonise with the architectural composition of the original property and is detrimental to the character, appearance and visual amenities of the street scene.  The proposal is therefore contrary to Policy BE1 of the Hillingdon Local Plan: Part One - Strategic Policies (November 2012), Policies DMHB 1, DMHB 2,  DMHB 11, DMHB 12 and DMHB 13 of the Hillingdon Local Plan Part Two - Development Management Policies (January 2020)  and the NPPF."
